body_text.text:
At the time of writing, Italy has the third highest number of COVID-19 cases after USA and Spain (Fig. 1
); consequently, its experience may be useful for other countries that have not yet had to face the full force of the disease. Lombardy is the Italian region with the highest number of recorded cases (34.507 as 1 of April1, or 47.3% of the total); the corresponding figures in the neighbouring regions of Emilia-Romagna and Veneto are respectively 10,008 (13.6%) and 6935 (9.4%). To the best of our knowledge, there are still no studies that have considered how to handle IBD and rheumatic patients with COVID-19. (See Table 1
.)
